data.enText: the ability or qualities necessary to do sth

data.chText: 动物园的动物已经丧失自己捕食的能力。
data.enText: Animals in the zoo have lost the capability to catch/of catching food for themselves.

data.chText: 超出了当前技术能力的范围；在当前技术能力的范围以内
data.enText: beyond/within the capabilities of current technology

data.chText: 年龄影响着一个人能力的大小。
data.enText: Age affects the range of a person's capabilities.
the power or weapons that a country has for war or for military action

data.chText: 英国的核力量 / 军事力量

ex.chText: 她有能力经营父亲的企业。
ex.enText: She has the ability to run her father's business.

ex.chText: 他显示出农耕方面的才能。
ex.enText: He shows an ability in/for farming.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，主要用于人，指在智力或体力上能够做某事的实际能力，常后接动词不定式或介词 in/for。

d: 能力，本领，能耐；专门技能

ex.chText: 她具备处理这项工作的能力。
ex.enText: She has the capability to handle the work.

ex.chText: 玛丽有能力成为一名出色的教师。
ex.enText: Mary has the capability of becoming an excellent teacher.

ex.chText: 她认为他做不了同声传译。
ex.enText: In her opinion, simultaneous translation is beyond his capabilities.

synonyms.bx: 尤指完成有难度的事情所需的能力，常后接动词不定式或介词 of，可以复数形式出现。

ex.chText: 他具有操作计算机的能力。
ex.enText: He has a capacity for computers.
The fuel tank has a capacity of 50 litres.

synonyms.bx: 指人理解或做某事的能力，或容器、房间等的容纳能力，常后接介词 of/for。

ex.chText: 你应当尽力保持自己的专业能力。
ex.enText: You should try to maintain your professional competence.

ex.chText: 我们怀疑他教书的能力。
ex.enText: We have doubt about his competence in teaching.

ex.chText: 他在处理这些问题时完全显示出了他的能力。
ex.enText: He demonstrated thorough competence in dealing with these issues.

synonyms.bx: 强调做某事的非凡能力，常后接介词 in。

tr: the quality of being capable -- physically or intellectually or legally
example: he worked to the limits of his capability

tr: an aptitude that may be developed
the susceptibility of something to a particular treatment
example: the capability of a metal to be fused

value.def: If you have the capability or the capabilities to do something, you have the ability or the qualities that are necessary to do it.

example.ex: People experience differences in physical and mental capability depending on the time of day...
example.tran: 在一天当中的不同时间,人的体力和脑力也会有所差异。

example.ex: The standards set four years ago in Seoul will be far below the athletes' capabilities now.
example.tran: 4年前在首尔制定的标准将远远低于目前运动员的水平。

gramarinfo.label: with supp, oft adj N, N to-inf

value.def: A country's military capability is its ability to fight in a war.

example.ex: Their military capability has been reduced because their air force has proved not to be effective...
example.tran: 由于空军战斗力不够强大，他们的军事实力有所下降。

example.ex: They have the capability to destroy the enemy in days rather than weeks.
example.tran: 他们有能力在几天内,而不是几个星期内消灭敌人。

gramarinfo.label: with supp, usu adj N, N to-inf

trans: (通常指制造核武器的)核能力，核力量
